MODULE: src/utils/ansi-adapter
FILES: ansi-adapter.js
RESPONSIBILITY: Strip ANSI escape codes and collapse carriage-return progress lines for Telegram display
KEY_FILES:
- ansi-adapter.js: 3 exported functions, ~100 lines. Pure string transformation, no I/O.
DEPENDENCIES:
- uses: none (no external dependencies)
- imported-by: src/bot/telegram.js (onAssistantChunk hook)
TRAPS:
- ANSI_REGEX must cover OSC sequences (ESC ] ... BEL), CSI sequences (ESC [ ... final), and simple two-char sequences — incomplete regex misses hyperlinks and window-title codes
- collapseCarriageReturns splits on \n first, then collapses \r within each line — do NOT split on \r globally or \r\n lines will be mangled
- processChunk applies stripAnsi THEN collapseCarriageReturns — order matters; reversing creates garbled output on ANSI-colored progress bars
- Returns '' for null/undefined inputs — callers should not rely on passthrough of falsy values
CHANGELOG:
- 2026-03-22 | add: initial module for F-020 ANSI stripping and progress-line collapsing
UPDATED: 2026-03-22
